      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CARDIGAN SNIPER (1) is a promising colt who was an impressive winner by 14m on debut at Bendigo then did well to come from a wide barrier and finish fourth in a handy line-up in the Rising Star at Ballarat last week. Much better served by the ace draw and looks hard to contain here. CLAYTON (6) is a colt by leading sire Captaintreacherous on debut for a good juvenile trainer in Michael Stanley. Chased Group 1 winner Jacwill Kid when runner-up in his latest trial at Menangle. Expect a strong showing. SEABREEZE LAD (3) draws well and is worth some thought after coming from the back row for a last-start win in a maiden at Globe Derby. BUILDTHEMANASTATUE (2) resumes after recording a win and a second in two Adelaide outings in his first campaign. Draws well so include.",
